ce:section.ce:para:
The successful preparation of poly(IA-co-PEGMA) and FSNPs-poly(IA-co-PEGMA) were confirmed by 1H NMR spectroscopy as a comparison. As shown in Fig. 1
                     , the characteristic chemical shift ranging from 3.32 to 3.80ppm is ascribed to the methylene groups of PEG and another characteristic chemical shift located in 4.26ppm is attributed to the methylene groups of IA. The others peaks at δ=0.82ppm (-CH3), δ=1.20ppm (CH2
                     ), and δ=1.94ppm (OCH3) are derived from the poly(IA-co-PEGMA). As compared with the 1H NMR spectrum of poly(IA-co-PEGMA), the characteristic chemical shift of FSNPs-poly(IA-co-PEGMA) located in 3.61ppm could be found because PEGMA could be dissolved in D2O. Therefore, these results confirmed that poly(IA-co-PEGMA) have been successfully conjugated onto the surface of silica nanoparticles (FSNPs-NH2) via ring-opening reaction.
